---
import ProductLayout from '@/layouts/ProductLayout.astro';
---

<ProductLayout
  title="BSNexus — AI Agent Orchestration"
  description="Throw an idea in, and it builds itself."
  locale="en"
  product="BSNexus"
  accent="#3b82f6"
  appUrl="https://nexus.bsvibe.dev"
>
  <h1>BSNexus</h1>
  <p class="product-tagline">Throw an idea in, and it builds itself. Build AI agent teams and automate complex workflows without code.</p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>

  <div class="feature-grid">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Agent Org Chart</h3>
      <p>Set up agent roles and relationships like a real team. Manager agents delegate tasks to subordinates automatically.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Goal-Based Execution</h3>
      <p>Define the outcome, and agents plan and execute autonomously. Focus on results, not processes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Multi-Engine Support</h3>
      <p>Claude, GPT, local LLMs — configure different engines for different agents based on their roles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Team Collaboration</h3>
      <p>Share agent configurations with your team and improve workflows together.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>No Code Required</h2>
  <p>BSNexus is designed for non-developers. Describe agent roles in natural language, set goals, and let the agents do the work.</p>

  <h2>Use Cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>PMs</strong> — Automated weekly reports, issue triage, sprint summaries</li>
    <li><strong>Marketers</strong> — Content research, draft writing, and scheduling on autopilot</li>
    <li><strong>Founders</strong> — Market research, competitor analysis, investor meeting prep by agent teams</li>
    <li><strong>Developers</strong> — Code review, documentation, CI/CD monitoring automation</li>
  </ul>
</ProductLayout>
